  "chapter": {
    "number": 28,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Where Can Wisdom Be Found?"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Surely there is a mine for silver",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and a place where gold is refined.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Iron is taken from the earth,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and copper is smelted from ore.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Man puts an end to the darkness;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "he probes the farthest recesses",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for ore in deepest darkness.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Far from human habitation he cuts a shaft",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in places forgotten by the foot of man.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Far from men he dangles and sways.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Food may come from the earth,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but from below it is transformed as by fire.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Its rocks are the source of sapphires,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "containing flecks of gold.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "No bird of prey knows that path;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "no falcon’s eye has seen it.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Proud beasts have never trodden it;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "no lion has ever prowled over it.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The miner strikes the flint;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "he overturns mountains at their base.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He hews out channels in the rocks,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and his eyes spot every treasure.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He stops up",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3184
          },
          {
            "text": "the sources of the streams",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to bring what is hidden to light.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But where can wisdom be found,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and where does understanding dwell?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "No man can know its value,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "nor is it found in the land of the living.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The ocean depths say, ‘It is not in me,’",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "while the sea declares, ‘It is not with me.’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "It cannot be bought with gold,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "nor can its price be weighed out in silver.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "It cannot be valued in the gold of Ophir,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in precious onyx or sapphire.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Neither gold nor crystal can compare to it,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "nor jewels of fine gold be exchanged for it.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Coral and quartz are unworthy of mention;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the price of wisdom is beyond rubies.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Topaz from Cush",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3185
          },
          {
            "text": "cannot compare to it,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "nor can it be valued in pure gold.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "From where then does wisdom come,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and where does understanding dwell?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "It is hidden from the eyes of every living thing",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and concealed from the birds of the air.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Abaddon",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3186
          },
          {
            "text": "and Death say,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "‘We have heard a rumor about it.’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But God understands its way,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and He knows its place.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For He looks to the ends of the earth",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and sees everything under the heavens.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When God fixed the weight of the wind",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and measured out the waters,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "when He set a limit for the rain",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and a path for the thunderbolt,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "then He looked at wisdom and appraised it;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He established it and searched it out.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 28,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "And He said to man, ‘Behold,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the fear of the Lord, that is wisdom,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and to turn away from evil is understanding.’”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
